.TH "sk_capable" 9 "sk_capable" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
sk_capable \- Socket global capability test
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "bool" sk_capable
.BI "(const struct sock *sk "  ","
.BI "int cap "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "sk" 12
Socket to use a capability on or through
.IP "cap" 12
The global capability to use
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
Test to see if the opener of the socket had when the socket was
created and the current process has the capability \fIcap\fP in all user
namespaces.
